PN,44804
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F448A1773346284
OL,3,CGerry Adams was 'de facto leader' of
OL,4,CIRA, court told
OL,6,FHe also said that if Mr Adams did not
OL,7,Fhold a high rank in the IRA, then he
OL,8,Fpulled off "a remarkable coup" in
OL,9,Fconvincing the British, Irish and US
OL,10,Fgovernments, as well as many IRA
OL,11,Fmembers, that he was.
OL,13,FThe witness added: "Had the defendant
OL,14,Fnot been the senior figure in the IRA
OL,15,Fthat he was, there would have been
OL,16,Fabsolutely no point in the British,
OL,17,FIrish and United States governments
OL,18,Fdealing with him the way they did on
OL,19,Fthe road to the Good Friday Agreement
OL,20,Fin 1998."
OL,26,@pD@LOUpD@^O]uD@TOU|D@IO]
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G4/14
