OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F448A1773346284
OL,3,CGerry Adams was 'de facto leader' of
OL,4,CIRA, court told
OL,6,FWitness B described the Army Council
OL,7,Fas a "very strong" and "disciplined"
OL,8,Fbody and that no attack, such as the
OL,9,Fbombings in London and Manchester,
OL,10,Fwould have taken place without its
OL,11,Fapproval.
OL,13,FHe said: "The operations outside
OL,14,FNorthern Ireland specifically required
OL,15,FArmy Council authority and especially
OL,16,Fsomething as significant as breaking
OL,17,Fthe ceasefire, that would have been
OL,18,Fauthorised by the Army Council,
OL,19,Fdecided on by the Army Council."
OL,26,@oD@FOUoD@RO]oD@XOUoD@dO]uD@JOU{D@`O]
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G7/14
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
