PN,44811
SC,0011
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F448A1773346284
OL,3,CGerry Adams was 'de facto leader' of
OL,4,CIRA, court told
OL,6,FAlso giving evidence was Timothy
OL,7,FHanley, a retired police officer from
OL,8,FNorthern Ireland.
OL,10,FIn a statement for the trial, he said
OL,11,Fhe had "information and intelligence"
OL,12,Fthat led him to believe Mr Adams
OL,13,Fdirected the Old Bailey and Docklands
OL,14,Fbombings.
OL,16,FMr Craven, in cross-examination, said:
OL,17,F"If you had information which created
OL,18,Fa reasonable suspicion that Mr Adams
OL,19,Fdirected those bombings, you would
OL,20,Fhave immediately contacted your
OL,21,Fcounterparts in London and Manchester."
OL,26,@sD@HOUsD@eO]yD@AOU}D@gO]
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}           G11/14
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
