CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F448A1773346284
OL,3,CGerry Adams was 'de facto leader' of
OL,4,CIRA, court told
OL,6,FMr Craven suggested he could have
OL,7,Fpicked up the phone to speak to
OL,8,Fofficers in England.
OL,10,FMr Hanley said: "I could have done it.
OL,11,FThe operational reality was that Mr
OL,12,FAdams, or anybody else I would say in
OL,13,Fthe IRA, would go for a no-comment
OL,14,Finterview and not speak.
OL,16,F"That is not making an excuse but that
OL,17,Fwas the operational reality."
OL,26,@rD@QOUxD@AOUyD@]O]
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}           G13/14
